# Vercel deploy ignore — what NOT to upload to Vercel.
#
# The Vercel site = static landing/ (built by scripts/copy-landing-for-vercel.mjs)
#                 + Python serverless functions in api/ (deps in api/requirements.txt).
# Everything else here is local-dev tooling and not needed for the deploy.

# === Critical: keep Vercel's uv sync away from the root project ===
# pyproject.toml + root requirements.txt declare heavy deps (playwright, resend,
# jinja2) for the local PDF delivery pipeline. Vercel does not need any of these
# for the lightweight webhook functions, and trying to install them breaks the
# function packaging step. Functions install only api/requirements.txt instead.
pyproject.toml
/requirements.txt
/requirements-automation.txt
/requirements-ui.txt

# === Local-dev directories not needed in the deploy ===
docs/
customers/
findings_library/
external/
tests/
output/
data/
drafts/
screenshots/
templates/
prompts/

# Shared lib/ is only used by local scripts, not the api/ functions
lib/

# === Local Python scripts (none run on Vercel) ===
scripts/audit_ui/
scripts/audit_ui.py
scripts/*.py

# === Sensitive files (env vars come from the Vercel platform) ===
.env
.env.local
.env.example

# === Build artifacts (generated fresh on each deploy) ===
dist/

# === Caches ===
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# === IDE / OS ===
.vscode/
.cursor/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
